I am pleased to announce the first beta version of the Caml Tk interface
for Tk 4.0. 
I am less pleased to announce that many changes make this version incompatible
with previous ones. But hell, it is already the case for Tk 4.0 vs. Tk 3.6.

Tk 4.0 is a lot more powerful than Tk 3.6 (xbm and GIF images loading,
embedded images and widgets in text, a wonderful gray background, ...)

MMM, a mind-boggling Web browser written with CamlTk4 will be released soon.

The library is available by anonymous ftp from ftp.inria.fr
For the sources:
directory lang/caml-light, file camltk4b1.tar.gz
For the documentation:
directory lang/caml-light, file camltk4b1.doc.tar.gz

Please report problems and bugs directly to me (Francois.Rouaix@inria.fr).
instead of caml mailing lists. Don't hesitate to make comments and
suggestions, or ask questions.

--
Francois.Rouaix@inria.fr                   Projet Cristal - INRIA Rocquencourt





